-# Test × Computer matrix for the Summary tab. Filters to
-# "interesting" rows only — failing, mixed, pending, or flagged
-# tests — since on commits with 100+ test cases the all-green
-# rows would dwarf the few that actually need attention. The
-# legend above shows every cell kind, and the user can switch to
-# the Tests tab for the unfiltered list.
-#
-# Locals:
-#   per_test:     output of `Commit#per_test_summary` (sorted
-#                 worst-first).
-#   per_computer: output of `Commit#per_computer_summary` (sorted
-#                 worst-first).
-#   branch:       Branch the commit lives on (for cell links).
-#   sha:          Short SHA of the commit (for cell links).

- # Cell-aware filter: a row is "interesting" if any of its
- # built-computer cells is not a clean pass (anything failing,
- # pending, or carrying an fpe/checksum/inlists_full flag).
- # Driving off the matrix instead of `row[:overall]` matters now
- # that pass-with-pending-neighbors classifies as :pass — we
- # still want to surface those rows so the user can see *which*
- # cells didn't report. The triage lives in CommitsHelper because
- # HAML can't carry multi-line case/if dispatch in a `- ...`
- # block.
- built_computer_ids = per_computer.select { |r| r[:built] }.map { |r| r[:computer_id] }
- interesting, clean_count, not_run_count = matrix_partition(per_test, built_computer_ids)
- computers = per_computer.map { |r| r[:computer] }.compact

%h3.font-semibold.text-fg.flex.items-center.gap-2 Test × Computer matrix
%p.text-fg-muted.text-sm.mt-1.mb-3
  Tests with failures, mixed results, pending submissions, or flags.
  - hide_parts = []
  - hide_parts << "#{clean_count} clean" if clean_count.positive?
  - hide_parts << "#{not_run_count} not yet run" if not_run_count.positive?
  - if hide_parts.any?
    %span.text-fg-subtle
      = "Hiding #{hide_parts.join(' and ')}."

= render "commits/matrix_legend"

- if computers.empty?
  .mt-4.rounded-md.border.border-border-subtle.bg-bg-subtle.px-4.py-6.text-center.text-fg-muted.text-sm
    No computers have submitted results for this commit yet.
- elsif interesting.empty? && clean_count.positive?
  .mt-4.rounded-md.border.border-border-subtle.bg-bg-subtle.px-4.py-6.text-center.text-fg-muted.text-sm
    All reported tests are passing on every computer. Nothing to investigate here.
- elsif interesting.empty?
  .mt-4.rounded-md.border.border-border-subtle.bg-bg-subtle.px-4.py-6.text-center.text-fg-muted.text-sm
    No test results yet — every test is still pending or blocked by a build failure.
- else
  .mt-4.overflow-x-auto
    .grid.gap-1{ style: "grid-template-columns: minmax(160px, 1fr) repeat(#{computers.size}, 22px); align-items: end;" }
      -# Header row: empty corner cell + vertical computer labels.
      %span &nbsp;
      - computers.each do |c|
        %span.font-mono.text-fg-subtle.justify-self-center{
          class: "text-[10px]",
          style: "writing-mode: vertical-rl; transform: rotate(180deg); height: 80px; line-height: 22px;",
          title: c.name }
          = c.name
      -# Body rows: test label + one cell per computer.
      - interesting.each do |row|
        - test_case = row[:test_case]
        - next unless test_case
        .min-w-0.font-mono.text-fg{ class: "text-[11px]" }
          %span.text-fg-subtle= "#{test_case.module}/"
          %span.truncate.inline-block.align-middle{ style: "max-width: 240px;" }= test_case.name
        - computers.each do |c|
          = render "commits/matrix_cell",
                   cell: row[:cells_by_computer][c.id],
                   test_case: test_case,
                   computer: c,
                   branch: branch,
                   sha: sha
